      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "feat: channel echo / session pinning",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n- Adds echo delivery infrastructure that mirrors session messages to additional channels\n- `SessionEchoTarget` type on `SessionEntry` for persistent echo target configuration\n- `message:sent` internal hook triggers echo delivery (fire-and-forget, no circular echo)\n- CLI: `openclaw sessions echo add/remove/list` subcommands\n- Gateway method: `sessions.echo` for programmatic pin/unpin (VituReClaw HUD)\n\n## Motivation\n\nSessions used across multiple transports (Telegram + VituReClaw glasses + web UI) result in fragmented chat logs. Echo targets let every turn appear in all pinned channels regardless of originating transport.\n\n## Files changed\n\n| File | Purpose |\n|------|--------|\n| `src/config/sessions/types.ts` | `SessionEchoTarget` type + `echoTargets` field |\n| `src/infra/outbound/echo.ts` | Core echo resolution + delivery |\n| `src/infra/outbound/echo-hook.ts` | Internal hook registration |\n| `src/commands/sessions-echo.ts` | CLI subcommands |\n| `src/gateway/server-methods/sessions.ts` | `sessions.echo` gateway method |\n| `src/gateway/server-methods.ts` | Method registration |\n| `src/gateway/server-startup-post-attach.ts` | Hook auto-registration at boot |\n| `src/cli/program/register.status-health-sessions.ts` | CLI command wiring |\n\n## Test plan\n\n- [ ] Unit test for `resolveEchoTargets` (deduplication, role filtering)\n- [ ] Integration test: add echo target via gateway method, send message, verify echo arrives\n- [ ] Verify circular echo prevention (echo delivery does not re-trigger hooks)\n- [ ] CLI smoke test: add/list/remove echo targets\n\nSupersedes #88386 (closed: branch had unrelated deployment commits).\n\n---\n\n## Proof (manual)\n\n> Mantis isn't triggerable with my repo access, so this is supplied manually. Ran this branch live on a real Telegram bot (Windows, real session store). Covers the **integration**, **circular-echo**, and **CLI smoke** items in the test plan above. Telegram chat id redacted as `<chat>`.\n\n**Build note:** the branch did not build/typecheck as-is — repaired in fd8ada2025 (now on this branch): duplicate `SessionsEchoParams`, stale `theme` import + `theme.bold`, `echoTargets` missing from the reserved slot-key list, and a wrong `.find`/`.filter` param annotation (`threadId` is `string|number`). `tsgo:core` clean after.\n\n**1. CLI `add` / `list` / `remove`** (real store, net-zero):\n```\n$ openclaw sessions echo add  --session-key …:thread:<chat>:67 --channel telegram --to <chat> --thread-id 26237 --label echo-proof\n  Added echo target: telegram -> <chat> (echo-proof)\n$ openclaw sessions echo list --session-key …:thread:<chat>:67 --json\n  { \"echoTargets\":[{ \"channel\":\"telegram\",\"to\":\"<chat>\",\"threadId\":\"26237\",\"label\":\"echo-proof\",\"addedAt\":… }] }\n$ openclaw sessions echo remove --session-key …:thread:<chat>:67 --channel telegram --to <chat> --thread-id 26237\n  Removed echo target: telegram -> <chat>\n$ openclaw sessions echo list --session-key …:thread:<chat>:67\n  No echo targets configured for this session.\n```\nRaw store reads confirmed `echoTargets: null → […] → null`.\n\n**2. Live cross-channel mirror** (source thread 67 → pinned thread 26237):\n```\n[telegram] Inbound message …direct, 12 chars                            ← user message in thread 67\n[telegram] outbound send ok messageId=36822 threadId=26237 silent=true  ← echoed to pinned thread\n[telegram] outbound send ok messageId=36824 threadId=26237 silent=true  ← echoed\n```\nEcho fires off `message:received`, independent of the agent turn.\n\n**3. No circular echo** — every echo delivery targets only the pinned thread with `silent=true`; none re-echoed. Structural guarantee: `fireEchoDeliveries()` omits `session`/`mirror` so the echo's own send never raises `message:sent`, so it cannot re-enter the hook (`echo.ts`).",
        "branch": "rfc/channel-echo",
